We discovered this  place after camping at az hot springs, we were too hungry to drive an hour to kingman, so we drove 20 miles or so out of the way and found this place.
Our server was super socially awkward, but the food was delightful.
Won ton soup was excellent.
My panang was actually spicy  ( I hate it when they think bc you're white that you can't handle spicy food so they make it bland).
My husband got their special which was a beef dish- also very good.
Thai iced tea was super sweet- and i like my sweet things.
Would definitely go here again if we were in the area.

