Little Dumpling changed a little bit since my last visit.
They still offer fresh, quick, hot very low priced entrees that include a cup of soup mostly priced at $5.50.
They dropped the side salad and the short menu and the scoop of rice is no longer heart shaped.
I enjoyed the ginger chicken last time so I decided to try it again.
The white meat chicken was still very moist and nicely prepared but they weren't spot on with the sauce this time as most of it lacked the ginger and was too heavy with soy sauce.
I tried a bite of the basil chicken.
It was very tasty and good but not what I know as basil chicken.
It was a different formula that wasn't as balanced as I like it with the garlic  chilies and fresh basil.
It seemed heavy with shrimp paste instead of fish sauce but it still tasted good.
I would still keep them on my rotation.
Not the best but much better than a lot of places.

